The TCoV levels of the fecal droppings on the floor assayed by RRT-PCR ranged from 104 to 2.8 × 106
 copies/μl from 1 to 14 DPI (Fig. 6
). The viral level in the feces on the floor was 2 log less than that from the cloacal fecal swabs. Higher levels of TCoV in the fecal droppings on the floor were detected at 3, 8, and 13 DPI, respectively.
